description: Permanently deletes a  GeoMatchSet. You can't delete a GeoMatchSet if it's still used in any Rules or if it still includes any countries. If you just want to remove a GeoMatchSet from a Rule, use  UpdateRule. To permanently delete a GeoMatchSet from AWS WAF, perform the following steps:

parameters.name: GeoMatchSetId
parameters.description: The GeoMatchSetID of the  GeoMatchSet that you want to delete. GeoMatchSetId is returned by  CreateGeoMatchSet and by  ListGeoMatchSets.

parameters.name: ChangeToken
parameters.description: The value returned by the most recent call to  GetChangeToken.

nested_items.name: ChangeToken
nested_items.description: The ChangeToken that you used to submit the DeleteGeoMatchSet request. You can also use this value to query the status of the request. For more information, see  GetChangeTokenStatus.
